question: What are the different customer ids?
Of those, who spent over 150 dollars in total?
sql: SELECT CustomerId FROM receipts GROUP BY CustomerId
SELECT T3.CustomerId FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.CustomerId HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  150
SELECT T3.CustomerId FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.CustomerId HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  150

paraphrase: What are the ids of customers who spend more than 5 on average for each good?
data.question: Find the ids of customers whose average spending for each good is above 5.

question: What are the different customer ids?
Of those, who spends over 5 dollars on average for each good?
sql: SELECT CustomerId FROM receipts GROUP BY CustomerId
SELECT T3.CustomerId FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.CustomerId HAVING avg(T1.price)  >  5

paraphrase: On what dates did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars worth of goods in total?
data.question: On which day did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars in total.

question: What are all the different dates on receipts?
Of these, which dates did the bakery sell more than 100 dollars of goods?
sql: SELECT date FROM receipts GROUP BY date
SELECT T3.date FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.date HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  100
SELECT T3.date FROM goods AS T1 JOIN items AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.item JOIN receipts AS T3 ON T2.receipt  =  T3.ReceiptNumber GROUP BY T3.date HAVING sum(T1.price)  >  100
